---
title: Fajita-Spiced Chicken with Zesty Black Bean Salad & Potato Wedges
description: Bold Tex-Mex flavors pump up tender pork chops with a smoky, slightly spicy kick. You'll whip up crispy roasted potato wedges and a zesty black bean salad with bell pepper, tomato, and scallions to complete this colorful meal that's packed with flavor and ready on the table in a speedy 20 minutes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67cebba86a498293bec85b1a-c815e126.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67d008cfbeb34419ba7b0c0a-en-US.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/fajita-spiced-chicken-67d008cfbeb34419ba7b0c0a
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 47 g
  fiber: 13 g
  sodium: 1060 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce. Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @oil{}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, core and dice @green bell pepper{1}(cored and diced) into 1/2-inch pieces. Dice @tomato{1}(diced) into 1/2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Drain and rinse @black beans{1}. Quarter @lime{1}(quartered).

In a #large bowl{}, toss together bell pepper, tomato, scallions, beans, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @fajita spice blend{1/2%tsp} (you'll use more later), @salt{1%tsp}, juice from three lime wedges, and pepper until well combined. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil, 1 tsp Fajita Spice Blend, 2 tsp salt, and juice from six lime wedges.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @fajita spice blend{2%tsp}, a pinch of salt, and pepper.

> Be sure to measure the Fajita Spice Blend - we sent more!

> Swap in pork chops or salmon for chicken. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or salmon (skin sides down) until skin is crisp, 5-7 minutes. Flip salmon and cook until cooked through, 1-2 minutes more.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat.

Add @butter{1%tbsp} to pan with chicken; baste chicken with melted butter until thoroughly coated.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP butter.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest at least ~{3%minutes}.

> You can start plating the potatoes and salad while the chicken rests.

Slice chicken crosswise.

> Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon!).

Divide chicken, potato wedges, and salad between plates in separate sections. Drizzle any remaining butter from pan over chicken. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.